.1 * f(0.35, 1.4235606640625) = 0.1 * (2*0.35 + 1.4235606640625) = 0.14235606640625\nk4 = 0.1 * f(0.4, 1.4920519375) = 0.1 * (2*0.4 + 1.4920519375) = 0.14920519375\ny_4 = 1.34980546875 + (0.134980546875 + 2*0.14172957421875 + 2*0.14235606640625 + 0.14920519375) / 6 = 1.4920519375\n\nThus, the approximation of y(0.4) using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with a step size of 0.1 is 1.4921 (rounded to four decimal places)."
